To convert the sentence "I have finished my homework." from present perfect to past perfect tense in MATLAB, you can write a simple script that replaces the present perfect structure with the past perfect structure. Here's a basic example of how you can achieve this:

```matlab
% Original sentence
original_sentence = 'I have finished my homework.';

% Replace present perfect with past perfect
past_perfect_sentence = strrep(original_sentence, 'have finished', 'had finished');

% Display the result
disp('Original Sentence:');
disp(original_sentence);
disp('Past Perfect Sentence:');
disp(past_perfect_sentence);
```

This script uses the `strrep` function to replace "have finished" with "had finished," converting the sentence to past perfect tense. Note that this script is designed specifically for this particular sentence structure and may need adjustments for other sentences or more complex grammar rules.
